<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/26616084-natasha-ahmed"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1442959232i/26616084._UX100_CR0,14,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/26616084-natasha-ahmed">Natasha Ahmed</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I wrote a blog post about this – the inspiration was a series of videos released in Karachi a few years ago. Young men and women were captured having <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I wrote a blog post about this – the inspiration was a series of videos released in Karachi a few years ago. Young men and women were captured having sex and necking in closed cabins of internet cafes. Almost all of the vitriol was unleashed on the women in the videos, none on the men. The double standard inspired me to write this story.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
