<div id="review_1141891714" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1141891714" />
    <a title="Tanisha Mehta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12675343-tanisha-mehta"><img alt="Tanisha Mehta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524637470p2/12675343.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1141891714?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tanisha Mehta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tanisha Mehta" href="/user/show/12675343-tanisha-mehta">Tanisha Mehta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12675343-tanisha-mehta?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12675343-tanisha-mehta?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12675343-tanisha-mehta?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12675343-tanisha-mehta?shelf=predictable">predictable</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1141891714" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17535771014079387271"><i>This book was provided by Indireads in exchange for an honest review</i><br/><br/>Firstly,I&apos;ve been trying to ignore this book for last 2 months because of my exams and project submissions (partly also because this was a romance/Contemporary book and I mostly tend to read this genre after I&apos;m done with some heavy series reading and I need something fluffy or meaningful to read)<br/><br/>This book is about Rumi&apos;s life,her choices,her decisions and consequences of her decisions. Rumi is in her early thirties with no love</span>
  <span id="freeText17535771014079387271" style="display:none"><i>This book was provided by Indireads in exchange for an honest review</i><br><br>Firstly,I've been trying to ignore this book for last 2 months because of my exams and project submissions (partly also because this was a romance/Contemporary book and I mostly tend to read this genre after I'm done with some heavy series reading and I need something fluffy or meaningful to read)<br><br>This book is about Rumi's life,her choices,her decisions and consequences of her decisions. Rumi is in her early thirties with no love life,living in a very conservative family.Her younger sister is living a married life in England with two kids.When Rumi's come to England to spend some time with her sister,Her friend hooks her up with a guy.<br><br>Ahad is in his late thirties,running a publishing company.He's scared of commitment.He's even more scared to fall for Rumi as she belongs to a conservative Pakistani family,who have commitment issues and belive that boys and girls should never be together before getting married.<br><br>As the story progresses,Rumi is falling for Ahad but she's scared for what her uncle in Karachi,her whole big family would think of her,if they find out about her spending time with a boy before Marriage.<br><br>I like the story,I really do.. but the third person PoV was a bit confusing. Once your reading what Rumi is feeling and then suddenly Ahad is thinking and elaborating his feelings and your just still confused as to why the sudden change in the PoVs?<br>I honestly had to go back up and read some lines again so I would know that the PoV was changed.<br><br>And the sex scenes.God.They were good and bad.I'm okay with reading them but then the way certain things were described and executed,you just felt like cringing. Idk maybe it was only me..<br><br><p>
  <i>Ahad tore through her delicate membrane and she cried out loud as pain paralyzed her. </i>
</p><br><a href="http://imgur.com/c4b3eTT" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1421070642i/13318068.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><br>*cringe*<br><br>That's just painful and you really don't feel like wanting to know more about their sex life.<br><br>-And the end.It was a really fast end I feel.We didnt even get to know what exactly happens to Rumi back at Karachi..the whole how she faces her Uncle and her Family<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Damn I was really looking forward to the fight.The drama.The conversation.How she faced the whole situation.But nothing.We get nothing.Only a summary of the events.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>I feel like that was a necessary part which as a reader I was really expecting to read.But it was probably<br>because its a novella and well writing more would increase the word count or probably the author didn't want Drama and fights between her Romance novella.<br><br>I really loved the plot.I feel that not only Pakistani girls feel restricted to be friends/go out with Boys.There are many countries,many places where interaction between Girls and boys is not allowed.I could relate to Rumi in some way.Many girls living in a Conservative family would relate to Rumi's problem,no matter what the age.<br>That's why I recommend it to everyone,willing to know a girl living conservative family 's problem,even though the writing isn't extraordinary,the plot is worth the read.</["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></span>
  <a data-text-id="17535771014079387271" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


