<div id="review_971171622" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/971171622" />
    <a title="Victoria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3604756-victoria"><img alt="Victoria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1300843902p2/3604756.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/971171622?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Victoria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Victoria" href="/user/show/3604756-victoria">Victoria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3604756-victoria?shelf=personal-choice-reads">personal-choice-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer971171622" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11884923973771897717">I picked up this novella on the recommendation of - someone, I can&apos;t quite remember who. Having been stuck in bed for two days and between review books, it seemed the right length to occupy a few of my hours. I am not sorry that I picked it up by any means. <br/><br/>This seems to be a light contemporary romance, and it certainly falls into that category. However, there is a bit more depth to it than that, with the main characters showing growth and enabling real empathy between themselves and the reader.</span>
  <span id="freeText11884923973771897717" style="display:none">I picked up this novella on the recommendation of - someone, I can't quite remember who. Having been stuck in bed for two days and between review books, it seemed the right length to occupy a few of my hours. I am not sorry that I picked it up by any means. <br /><br />This seems to be a light contemporary romance, and it certainly falls into that category. However, there is a bit more depth to it than that, with the main characters showing growth and enabling real empathy between themselves and the reader. The exploration of cultural norms and conflicting value systems adds depth as well. Although it follows the formula of contemporary romance, the path to happy ever after is not the norm and the main characters experience real change and acknowledgement of personal flaws.<br /><br />There are problems with this novella as you would expect from an author on their maiden voyage to novella-dom. Repetitive adjective use began to sound cliche, and the shifting point of view from paragraph to paragraph was frustrating to read. Secondary characters did not get the fleshing out they needed to make radical changes in position seem realistic. These are all issues that would be dealt with by tighter editing and experience. I do believe this author shows promise and will pick up further works.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11884923973771897717" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

