<div id="review_1135983321" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1135983321" />
    <a title="Ipshita Ranjana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10104072-ipshita-ranjana"><img alt="Ipshita Ranjana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1391940412p2/10104072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1135983321?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ipshita Ranjana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ipshita Ranjana" href="/user/show/10104072-ipshita-ranjana">Ipshita Ranjana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10104072-ipshita-ranjana?shelf=favorite">favorite</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1135983321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer843023770040876358">Butterfly Season is a coming of age romance.It follows the protagonist Rumi,as she struggles to find her own identity in a society filled with suffocating rules.Its a fight between what is considered right and what is right according to her. Rumi&apos;s journey is incredible and filled with all kinds of emotions.When the journey was this good,the end destination was even more beautiful.Personally for me the ending has to be the best part and I was not disappointed!<br/><br/>To summarize,Rumi meets Ahad while o</span>
  <span id="freeText843023770040876358" style="display:none">Butterfly Season is a coming of age romance.It follows the protagonist Rumi,as she struggles to find her own identity in a society filled with suffocating rules.Its a fight between what is considered right and what is right according to her. Rumi's journey is incredible and filled with all kinds of emotions.When the journey was this good,the end destination was even more beautiful.Personally for me the ending has to be the best part and I was not disappointed!<br /><br />To summarize,Rumi meets Ahad while on a vacation in London and they enter into a kind live in relationship involving loads of sex. Rumi's family,being the conservative kind and rules abiding people do not approve her "unholy" relationship and she is confused about whether her relationship with Ahad is right considering his commitment phobic nature and her society's strict rules.The story spans from London to Karachi as Rumi tries to find her own destiny.<br /><br /><br />The story had everything and was so much more than a romance.Technically this would be Ahad and Rumi's story but for me Rumi was the star and I loved her throughout.A stunning debut by Natasha Ahmed which proves that a romance can be so much more.Highly recommended for everyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="843023770040876358" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


