<div id="review_1160882898" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1160882898" />
    <a title="Book Ninja" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11117799-book-ninja"><img alt="Book Ninja" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530361640p2/11117799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1160882898?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Book Ninja" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Book Ninja" href="/user/show/11117799-book-ninja">Book Ninja</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1160882898" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15481442580213197136">This book was given to me as part of the Reviewer Program by Indireads. I really enjoyed reading it. This book is about breaking the boundaries that are surrounding you and taking a step towards freedom. It&apos;s about taking a stand for yourself and not being worried about what people will say. <br/><br/>This book is very true to reality. Firstly, the way Karachi was described in a positive light in this book, it felt good to read about my city in such a way. Karachi is beautiful and vibrant but the media us</span>
  <span id="freeText15481442580213197136" style="display:none">This book was given to me as part of the Reviewer Program by Indireads. I really enjoyed reading it. This book is about breaking the boundaries that are surrounding you and taking a step towards freedom. It's about taking a stand for yourself and not being worried about what people will say. <br /><br />This book is very true to reality. Firstly, the way Karachi was described in a positive light in this book, it felt good to read about my city in such a way. Karachi is beautiful and vibrant but the media usually just talks about how bad it is. Secondly, the description of the joint family system and how they meddle in your life. How being worried about what others will say or how reputations will be affected by making your own decisions for your own life. This is the root cause of all the problems in our society. If we let each other be, we can be a happy bunch of people. And lastly, the way Mahira was so helpful for Rumi and would do anything for Rumi's happiness. She was not just a friend, she was like a sister to her.<br /><br />These novellas by Indireads are fun to read. They are really good for light reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15481442580213197136" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


