<span id="freeTextContainer8753650721213107306">Natasha Ahmed is a pen name. In real life, Natasha is a graphic designer, a businesswoman and occasionally writes art and book reviews for publications within Pakistan. <br/><br/>She works in a small office at home, not far from Sea View, Karachi. From a tiny window, she can see the Arabian Sea sparkling in the distance, and small fishing boats trawl up and down the water throughout the day. When she’s not </span>
  <span id="freeText8753650721213107306" style="display:none">Natasha Ahmed is a pen name. In real life, Natasha is a graphic designer, a businesswoman and occasionally writes art and book reviews for publications within Pakistan. <br /><br />She works in a small office at home, not far from Sea View, Karachi. From a tiny window, she can see the Arabian Sea sparkling in the distance, and small fishing boats trawl up and down the water throughout the day. When she’s not writing books, she’s dreaming of setting sail towards the horizon and never looking back. Great adventure, she believes, starts with great daring.<br /><br />Butterfly Season is her first novella, though not, she hopes, her last.<br /><br />Find out more on Facebook: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://Facebook.com/tasha.author">http://Facebook.com/tasha.author</a>.<br /><br />Follow her on Twitter:<br />@NatashaA_Author</span>
